      },
      "date": "2012-04-11 01:26:06.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nIt looks like the RHEL 6 build was OK, but the RHEL 5 build failed due to selinux_is_enabled() not being declared on that kernel. This will need a configure check in lustre/autoconf/lustre_core.m4 to see if this function is declared in selinux.h or not. If not, then a simple static inline function to return 0 should be declared in lustre_compat25.h.\n\nThere are lots of examples to follow in those files, but feel free to ask if you have any questions.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "5016d1ff09f4785da5428e4d4ee2502513adb8b2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 250,
